1
00:00:19,166 --> 00:00:20,708
[CASTAL]
Duke Hybranz.

2
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:24,291
Your actions at the ceremony
were selfless and noble.

3
00:00:24,375 --> 00:00:26,583
You’re an exemplary,
loyal subject.

4
00:00:26,666 --> 00:00:28,875
I’m unworthy of such praise.

5
00:00:28,958 --> 00:00:31,250
My only concern was
for the Prime Minister.

6
00:00:31,333 --> 00:00:33,125
It was my greatest pleasure
to protect him

7
00:00:33,208 --> 00:00:34,916
from the attempt
made on his life,

8
00:00:35,000 --> 00:00:37,916
and to set his
Imperial Majesty’s mind at ease.

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:39,916
I escaped death
because of you.

10
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:42,458
And for that,
you have my eternal gratitude.

11
00:00:42,541 --> 00:00:45,166
I did what anyone else
would in my situation.

12
00:00:45,250 --> 00:00:47,291
While it’s true I’ll never
be one of the heroic

13
00:00:47,375 --> 00:00:49,333
Seven Knights
like Duke Kal-O,

14
00:00:49,416 --> 00:00:51,875
I was once a soldier.
That will never change.

15
00:00:51,958 --> 00:00:54,250
Ray Dawn?

16
00:00:54,333 --> 00:00:56,958
There was a time the man
was a brave fighter.

17
00:00:57,041 --> 00:00:58,416
No longer, it seems.

18
00:01:01,333 --> 00:01:02,791
[CASTAL]
Name your request.

19
00:01:02,875 --> 00:01:05,208
Is there anything
that you desire?

20
00:01:05,291 --> 00:01:06,875
Sire...

21
00:01:08,125 --> 00:01:10,291
I wish to be
given a fairy weapon.

22
00:01:10,375 --> 00:01:11,791
[gasps]

23
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:15,208
What? A Fairy Weapon? But why?

24
00:01:15,291 --> 00:01:17,291
♪

25
00:02:59,083 --> 00:03:01,791
I heard the news.
Busy day.

26
00:03:01,875 --> 00:03:04,041
You guys had your hands
full at the ceremony.

27
00:03:04,125 --> 00:03:07,333
Sure. But, I mean,
I didn’t really do much.

28
00:03:07,416 --> 00:03:09,250
Team spirit
has definitely improved.

29
00:03:09,333 --> 00:03:10,833
They have you to thank for that.

30
00:03:10,916 --> 00:03:13,041
Even we can tell a difference.

31
00:03:13,125 --> 00:03:16,500
Well, you know,
we all try our best.

32
00:03:16,583 --> 00:03:18,541
[gulping]

33
00:03:18,625 --> 00:03:20,708
[GONZALEZ sighs]

34
00:03:20,791 --> 00:03:22,041
[GONZALEZ]
Figures.

35
00:03:22,125 --> 00:03:25,458
The War of Unification
ended ten years ago,

36
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:27,750
but looks like another
one’s headed our way.

37
00:03:27,833 --> 00:03:29,583
-[MARLYA] What?
-[RYLAN] The question is

38
00:03:29,666 --> 00:03:31,750
will Kal-o or Hybranz start it?

39
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:34,541
My money’s on the former,
Kal-o is the shady one.

40
00:03:38,541 --> 00:03:40,541
-[wind whistling]
-[flag rustling]

41
00:03:45,958 --> 00:03:47,333
Is that so?

42
00:03:47,416 --> 00:03:49,333
Diese’s making his move.

43
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:52,375
Tell me what you know.

44
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,500
♪

45
00:04:00,416 --> 00:04:03,125
We’ll have Fairy Minister Sett
take responsibility

46
00:04:03,208 --> 00:04:04,583
for the events that transpired

47
00:04:04,666 --> 00:04:06,458
during the anniversary
celebration.

48
00:04:06,541 --> 00:04:09,333
Vice-Minister,
you’ll succeed him.

49
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:10,708
Sir.

50
00:04:11,791 --> 00:04:13,375
For his bravery,

51
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:16,416
Duke Hybranz has asked to be
given one of the Fairy Weapons.

52
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:17,958
I’m sorry?

53
00:04:18,041 --> 00:04:20,166
[GOLBARN] He intends to use it
to guard His Majesty,

54
00:04:20,250 --> 00:04:22,250
should such a situation arise.

55
00:04:22,333 --> 00:04:24,208
That’s a pretext, of course.

56
00:04:24,291 --> 00:04:26,666
Duke Kal-o is
one of the Seven Knights,

57
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:30,000
and therefore already has one of
these weapons in his possession.

58
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:31,708
Duke Hybranz does not.

59
00:04:31,791 --> 00:04:34,375
Obviously, there’s
an imbalance of power.

60
00:04:34,458 --> 00:04:36,583
[NEIN] May I ask
what you intend to do?

61
00:04:37,708 --> 00:04:40,208
Grant his wish.
Vice Minister Bellwood,

62
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:42,875
you’re to remove
a Fairy Weapon from the vault.

63
00:04:42,958 --> 00:04:44,791
Dorothea will transport it.

64
00:04:44,875 --> 00:04:46,708
Sound good, Director Auler?

65
00:04:46,791 --> 00:04:48,250
Sir.

66
00:04:50,125 --> 00:04:51,708
[NEIN]
Just what we needed.

67
00:05:00,083 --> 00:05:02,666
[metal gate scraping]

68
00:05:19,416 --> 00:05:22,333
So, um,
these Fairy Weapons,

69
00:05:22,416 --> 00:05:24,833
they were used during
the War of Unification

70
00:05:24,916 --> 00:05:26,500
by each of the Seven Knights?

71
00:05:26,583 --> 00:05:27,833
You got it.

72
00:05:34,708 --> 00:05:35,916
[gasps]

73
00:05:37,791 --> 00:05:40,666
[GRIFF] Painsealer.
Fratanil.

74
00:05:40,750 --> 00:05:43,625
Verosteal. Aliadra.

75
00:05:44,791 --> 00:05:47,416
Many Fairy Soldiers
were cut down by these armaments

76
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:48,791
while fighting in the war.

77
00:05:48,875 --> 00:05:50,416
Of the seven weapons
in existence,

78
00:05:50,500 --> 00:05:53,166
four of them are housed here,
deep inside our vault.

79
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,291
The Ministry of Fairies

80
00:05:54,375 --> 00:05:56,500
maintains strict control
over them.

81
00:05:56,583 --> 00:05:59,125
Doesn’t Ray Dawn
have one of the missing three?

82
00:05:59,208 --> 00:06:00,958
Yes. The Sororias.

83
00:06:01,041 --> 00:06:04,208
Incidentally, our own Director
Nein is one the Knights.

84
00:06:04,291 --> 00:06:08,250
-She owns the weapon Aliadra.
-Oh. I had no idea.

85
00:06:08,333 --> 00:06:10,916
I remember hearing a member
of the Seven was a woman.

86
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:13,708
But her?
The Director really is amazing.

87
00:06:13,791 --> 00:06:16,708
And if I’m not mistaken,
Verosteal belongs to you.

88
00:06:16,791 --> 00:06:19,375
Not quite. I’m not a Knight.

89
00:06:19,458 --> 00:06:21,000
Just looking after it.

90
00:06:22,166 --> 00:06:23,166
[FREE sighs]

91
00:06:24,375 --> 00:06:27,500
So, we’re giving Fratanil
to Duke Hybranz, right?

92
00:06:27,583 --> 00:06:30,791
[GRIFF] Yes. It was once used
by Garlan Battle,

93
00:06:30,875 --> 00:06:32,958
chief amongst
the Seven Knights.

94
00:06:33,041 --> 00:06:35,625
I wonder what the Duke
intends to use it for.

95
00:06:36,916 --> 00:06:38,916
♪

96
00:06:51,125 --> 00:06:53,375
[BEEVEE] From this angle,
Rondacia looks striking.

97
00:06:56,125 --> 00:06:59,250
[DIESE] It’s only a matter of
time before this crown jewel

98
00:06:59,333 --> 00:07:01,458
is within our reach.

99
00:07:01,541 --> 00:07:04,125
[BEEVEE] I’m in for one hell
of a spectacle, aren’t I?

100
00:07:04,208 --> 00:07:06,500
[DIESE] After all the trouble
I went through setting this up,

101
00:07:06,583 --> 00:07:08,083
I certainly hope so, Colonel.

102
00:07:10,125 --> 00:07:12,125
As do I. I’m counting on it.

103
00:07:24,125 --> 00:07:26,375
You’re carrying
a national treasure.

104
00:07:26,458 --> 00:07:28,541
Make certain that
it’s delivered safely.

105
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:29,750
[ALL]
Ma’am!

106
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:31,833
Dang. Hapstadt, huh?

107
00:07:31,916 --> 00:07:34,458
-I wish I was going.
-Take my place then.

108
00:07:34,541 --> 00:07:37,541
I’ll pass, thank you.
Sounds pretty intense.

109
00:07:37,625 --> 00:07:38,791
[KLARA sighs]

110
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:42,333
-You be careful.
-Thanks. We will.

111
00:07:42,416 --> 00:07:44,041
[OZZ chuckles]

112
00:07:52,125 --> 00:07:55,083
I hear you’re remaining behind.
Such a pity.

113
00:07:55,166 --> 00:07:57,000
I’m leaving you
in capable hands.

114
00:07:57,083 --> 00:08:00,083
They’ll see that Fratanil
reaches its destination.

115
00:08:00,166 --> 00:08:01,666
You may rest assured.

116
00:08:01,750 --> 00:08:04,458
[MEN grunting]

117
00:08:07,708 --> 00:08:09,750
It’s difficult to imagine
the amount of sweat

118
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:12,000
and blood it took
for us to have peace.

119
00:08:12,083 --> 00:08:15,500
I doubt anyone
would want to spill more.

120
00:08:17,125 --> 00:08:19,958
-[bell ringing]
-[horn blowing]

121
00:08:24,458 --> 00:08:26,916
♪

122
00:08:27,000 --> 00:08:29,000
[horn blowing]

123
00:08:37,166 --> 00:08:39,166
♪

124
00:09:09,166 --> 00:09:11,208
♪

125
00:09:18,583 --> 00:09:20,916
♪

126
00:09:30,833 --> 00:09:33,291
This place seems so empty
without any artificial fairies

127
00:09:33,375 --> 00:09:34,750
patrolling the grounds.

128
00:09:34,833 --> 00:09:37,333
The reliability of all
the models is in question.

129
00:09:37,416 --> 00:09:39,458
Thanks to the recent incidents.

130
00:09:39,541 --> 00:09:42,041
I don’t see how things
around here could get worse.

131
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:43,875
Except maybe a war.

132
00:09:43,958 --> 00:09:46,208
I’d appreciate it
if you didn’t jinx us!

133
00:09:46,291 --> 00:09:47,875
[SERGE laughing]

134
00:09:54,875 --> 00:09:57,208
Tell me what led you
to start working with Arcame?

135
00:09:59,416 --> 00:10:00,833
Who can say?

136
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:03,166
You were in contact
with Wolf-ran Row,

137
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:04,458
is that correct?

138
00:10:06,625 --> 00:10:08,416
Your plan failed,

139
00:10:08,500 --> 00:10:11,291
which means you’ll probably
avoid the death penalty

140
00:10:11,375 --> 00:10:13,791
if you tell me
everything you know.

141
00:10:13,875 --> 00:10:15,750
I’m sure I’ll spend
the rest of my life in jail.

142
00:10:15,833 --> 00:10:16,666
What’s the point?

143
00:10:16,750 --> 00:10:17,958
Cooperating with us

144
00:10:18,041 --> 00:10:19,666
could help reduce your sentence.

145
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,958
You might even get
the chance to start over.

146
00:10:23,416 --> 00:10:25,333
Listen. Ted.

147
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:27,666
When I spoke to Hanns he said
you were like a son to him,

148
00:10:27,750 --> 00:10:28,708
but he failed you.

149
00:10:28,791 --> 00:10:29,791
[gasps]

150
00:10:31,208 --> 00:10:34,041
[CHASE] If not for you,
come clean for his sake.

151
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:36,250
[sniffling]

152
00:10:36,333 --> 00:10:37,666
What’ve I done?

153
00:10:46,750 --> 00:10:49,000
[SOPHIE] See that?
The sun is nearly set.

154
00:10:50,875 --> 00:10:55,250
Unless blood flows or is spilt,
it remains stagnant.

155
00:10:56,416 --> 00:10:59,875
And until the day a person dies,
then they simply rot.

156
00:11:00,875 --> 00:11:03,666
Sophie.
Do you plan on dying?

157
00:11:05,041 --> 00:11:07,916
[SOPHIE] Anytime, as long
as it’s next to you.

158
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,875
[BEEVEE chuckles]

159
00:11:09,958 --> 00:11:11,208
[gasping]

160
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,750
Don’t worry about that one.

161
00:11:29,083 --> 00:11:31,250
[paper rustling]

162
00:11:34,208 --> 00:11:37,458
So, Nein Auler is unable
to leave Rondacia?

163
00:11:37,541 --> 00:11:38,666
[paper tearing]

164
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:41,000
I’d remark how small
your force is,

165
00:11:41,083 --> 00:11:42,708
yet, that’s never stood between

166
00:11:42,791 --> 00:11:44,833
you and your goals before,
has it?

167
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:46,083
[BEEVEE]
You’re welcome to join us

168
00:11:46,166 --> 00:11:48,000
if you’re looking for
some amusement.

169
00:11:48,083 --> 00:11:49,125
What do you say?

170
00:11:49,208 --> 00:11:51,500
Well, I would,
if it were my job.

171
00:11:51,583 --> 00:11:53,375
[chuckles]

172
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:02,041
[horn blowing]

173
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:09,833
[gasping]

174
00:12:11,125 --> 00:12:12,625
I didn’t mean to.

175
00:12:12,708 --> 00:12:18,166
Huh? Oh, that? You’re fine.
Don’t worry about it.

176
00:12:19,541 --> 00:12:24,041
Okay. Thanks.
If you say so. I guess.

177
00:12:30,458 --> 00:12:31,791
Won’t be long now.

178
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:41,625
♪

179
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:43,333
There’s someone on the tracks!

180
00:12:43,416 --> 00:12:45,375
-[horn blowing]
-[screaming]

181
00:12:46,416 --> 00:12:48,416
-The hell?
-[horn blowing]

182
00:12:48,500 --> 00:12:50,500
Get out of the way!
Do you want to die?

183
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:52,708
-[gunshot]
-[CONDUCTOR grunts]

184
00:12:52,791 --> 00:12:54,833
♪

185
00:12:54,916 --> 00:12:57,041
Let’s go.
Eizenkopf!

186
00:12:59,708 --> 00:13:01,208
[roaring]

187
00:13:01,291 --> 00:13:06,458
[train crashing, scraping]

188
00:13:16,458 --> 00:13:18,708
-[train crashing]
-[grunts]

189
00:13:18,791 --> 00:13:20,958
[screaming]

190
00:13:23,625 --> 00:13:25,625
♪

191
00:13:38,833 --> 00:13:40,833
[fire crackling]

192
00:13:48,875 --> 00:13:51,083
I'd be dead
if it wasn’t for you.

193
00:13:53,208 --> 00:13:55,166
Get some rest, child.

194
00:13:55,250 --> 00:13:57,125
[breathing heavily]

195
00:14:13,166 --> 00:14:14,750
[MARLYA whimpering]

196
00:14:17,250 --> 00:14:18,541
[gunshot]

197
00:14:23,583 --> 00:14:24,958
[MARLYA gasps]

198
00:14:32,291 --> 00:14:33,125
[MARLYA whimpers]

199
00:14:40,041 --> 00:14:42,541
Let no part of a kill
go to waste.

200
00:14:42,625 --> 00:14:44,166
Never forget that.

201
00:14:46,625 --> 00:14:48,458
[crying]

202
00:14:57,458 --> 00:14:59,916
[fire crackling]

203
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:05,291
[VICTOR coughing, wheezing]

204
00:15:07,583 --> 00:15:10,125
I’m such a burden.
Forgive me.

205
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:14,500
There’s nothing to forgive.
Get some rest, Victor.

206
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:25,500
[breathing shakily]

207
00:15:29,666 --> 00:15:31,958
[crying]

208
00:15:33,791 --> 00:15:35,041
[MARLYA] I don’t know
why I thought

209
00:15:35,125 --> 00:15:36,708
this time would be different.

210
00:15:40,708 --> 00:15:43,708
Turns out everyone
was right about me.

211
00:15:43,791 --> 00:15:45,625
I’m a cursed child.

212
00:15:45,708 --> 00:15:47,958
[FREE]
Marlya! Marlya!

213
00:15:48,041 --> 00:15:49,041
[bullets whizzing]

214
00:15:49,125 --> 00:15:50,583
Come on!
You’ve got to get up!

215
00:15:50,666 --> 00:15:51,958
[metal clanging]

216
00:15:52,041 --> 00:15:55,916
-Anything broken?
-No. I think I’m fine.

217
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:58,291
[FREE grunting]

218
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:06,791
[FREE] Third Unit,
guard Fratanil!

219
00:16:06,875 --> 00:16:08,833
We’re under attack.

220
00:16:08,916 --> 00:16:10,625
-Can you fight?
-Sir.

221
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:15,833
-[ricochet]
-[gunshots]

222
00:16:19,208 --> 00:16:20,041
[MARLYA grunts]

223
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:24,333
Free, I’ve spotted around ten to
fifteen enemies, a small force.

224
00:16:24,416 --> 00:16:26,666
Probably derailed us
to get the Fairy Weapon.

225
00:16:26,750 --> 00:16:28,375
Who’s got eyes on Hybranz?

226
00:16:28,458 --> 00:16:31,666
Ah, shit. Securing Fratanil’s
our first priority.

227
00:16:31,750 --> 00:16:33,416
We’ve got to fight.

228
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:34,875
-I’ll go.
-[MARLYA inhales sharply]

229
00:16:35,958 --> 00:16:37,750
Ozz. We’ve got you covered.

230
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,750
[gunshots]

231
00:16:40,833 --> 00:16:43,291
♪

232
00:16:53,375 --> 00:16:54,791
[FREE] Him?
Out of all the people

233
00:16:54,875 --> 00:16:55,958
in the whole damn world,

234
00:16:56,041 --> 00:16:57,791
why’d he have to
attack our train?

235
00:16:57,875 --> 00:16:59,250
[MARLYA]
Who is he?

236
00:16:59,333 --> 00:17:02,291
[FREE] Beevee Liscar,
one of the Seven Knights!

237
00:17:03,666 --> 00:17:06,083
He fought against Unification
until the very end.

238
00:17:06,166 --> 00:17:07,416
A Knight?

239
00:17:07,500 --> 00:17:09,541
Then does that mean
he has a Fairy Weapon?

240
00:17:12,541 --> 00:17:16,416
Stop cowering!
Come out and stop me, Dorothea!

241
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,666
That’s Gaddfacs,
the seventh weapon.

242
00:17:18,750 --> 00:17:21,750
Each of them is
a fairy’s worst nightmare.

243
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:23,916
Not to mention
he’s also got Eizenkopf.

244
00:17:24,958 --> 00:17:27,250
[FREE] I’ve no choice
but to use Fratanil.

245
00:17:27,333 --> 00:17:30,000
None of us are making it
out of here alive, otherwise.

246
00:17:31,791 --> 00:17:34,083
♪

247
00:17:34,166 --> 00:17:36,375
[gunshots]

248
00:17:36,458 --> 00:17:38,583
We’ve got to draw
out the enemy. Move.

249
00:17:41,541 --> 00:17:43,000
Look at these pebbles.

250
00:17:46,250 --> 00:17:47,791
-[MARLYA gasps]
-Lily!

251
00:17:49,208 --> 00:17:51,708
-[metal crashing]
-[Dorothea screaming]

252
00:17:51,791 --> 00:17:53,166
[MARLYA]
It’s too dangerous!

253
00:17:56,416 --> 00:17:59,458
-[roaring]
-Oh?

254
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:03,416
[roaring]

255
00:18:15,333 --> 00:18:17,666
-[fairy groans]
-[Ozz groans]

256
00:18:23,583 --> 00:18:25,416
Turn to dust, you pebble!

257
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:26,750
[OZZ grunts]

258
00:18:29,625 --> 00:18:31,958
-[BEEVEE shouting]
-[fairy screams]

259
00:18:32,041 --> 00:18:33,000
[groans]

260
00:18:43,583 --> 00:18:47,541
Armed with Fratanil? Bold move!
Won’t matter.

261
00:18:53,708 --> 00:18:55,791
Picking up that weapon
doesn’t make you a Knight!

262
00:19:03,916 --> 00:19:07,000
Guess it’s asking a lot for a
pebble to suddenly become steel.

263
00:19:07,083 --> 00:19:08,666
-[fairy summoned]
-Huh?

264
00:19:10,333 --> 00:19:11,833
-A fairy?
-Huh?

265
00:19:12,916 --> 00:19:14,125
[screaming]

266
00:19:16,208 --> 00:19:18,125
A truly pathetic display.

267
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:20,125
Perhaps next time
will be different.

268
00:19:20,208 --> 00:19:21,208
Sophie!

269
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,958
♪

270
00:19:32,083 --> 00:19:33,958
[MARLYA screams]

271
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:35,666
[gunshot]

272
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:42,333
[shouting]

273
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,583
-[OZZ panting]
-[MARLYA groans]

274
00:19:47,291 --> 00:19:49,250
Sorry, nothing personal.

275
00:19:51,166 --> 00:19:53,083
[screaming]

276
00:19:59,625 --> 00:20:01,000
[grunts]

277
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:06,125
[FREE shouting]

278
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:12,666
The mediocre should learn
from their failures.

279
00:20:13,666 --> 00:20:16,166
If you can’t turn humiliation
into strength,

280
00:20:16,250 --> 00:20:17,541
next time, you will die.

281
00:20:17,625 --> 00:20:20,291
-[gunshots]
-[OZZ groaning]

282
00:20:29,375 --> 00:20:32,958
[BEEVEE] You, on the other hand,
what a show.

283
00:20:33,041 --> 00:20:35,291
While it’s possible I would’ve
enjoyed fighting you

284
00:20:35,375 --> 00:20:36,791
on another occasion...

285
00:20:36,875 --> 00:20:39,791
Ozz... run.

286
00:20:39,875 --> 00:20:43,583
Your wounds are too severe
for second chances.

287
00:20:43,666 --> 00:20:45,708
You die tonight.

288
00:20:46,958 --> 00:20:48,791
[screams]

289
00:20:48,875 --> 00:20:50,666
[whimpering]

290
00:22:21,500 --> 00:22:23,500
[thundering]

291
00:22:32,500 --> 00:22:36,375
[MEN groaning]

292
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:41,500
[gasping, wheezing]

293
00:22:45,541 --> 00:22:47,875
Please, hold on.

294
00:22:50,875 --> 00:22:52,791
[OZZ screams, groans]

295
00:22:52,875 --> 00:22:54,791
No, Ozz, please no.

296
00:23:02,791 --> 00:23:04,791
[breathing shakily]

297
00:23:15,500 --> 00:23:16,666
[breathing stops]

298
00:23:19,416 --> 00:23:20,708
[MARLYA]
Ozz?

299
00:23:21,791 --> 00:23:23,375
No, this...

300
00:23:23,458 --> 00:23:25,125
This isn’t happening.

301
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:28,458
Open your eyes!

302
00:23:28,541 --> 00:23:31,166
[MARLYA crying]

303
00:23:33,250 --> 00:23:36,250
[MARLYA wailing]
Ozz!

304
00:23:39,125 --> 00:23:41,166
[MARLYA] I don’t want it to be
my fault that someone dies!

305
00:23:41,250 --> 00:23:42,916
[SERGE] I wonder if Marlya
will come back.

306
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,916
[FREE] We’re not a family,
but we are comrades

307
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,583
who watch each other’s backs.

308
00:23:46,666 --> 00:23:48,500
[MARLYA]
I can’t do it anymore.

